## Repair

Keeps filenames, lists, and deploy manifest in sync after manual edits.

```bash
aifabrix repair {{appName}}
```

Useful flags: `--dry-run`, `--auth <method>`, `--rbac`, `--expose`, `--sync`, `--test`.

## Enterprise AI Certification

Product-facing commands that prove operational readiness, AI trust, governance enforcement, and an **Enterprise AI Certification** report. Run after [publish](#publish-and-credentials).

| Command | What it proves |
| --- | --- |
| `aifabrix verify-operations {{appName}}` | Operational readiness — orchestrates validate, unit test, integration, and E2E for the whole system |
| `aifabrix verify-trust {{appName}}` | AI business context confidence (semantic agent metadata; not live vendor API calls) |
| `aifabrix verify-governance {{appName}}` | Policy coverage and ABAC enforcement scenarios (governed search key sets) |
| `aifabrix lifecycle {{appName}}` | Certification report from persisted pillar results on the dataplane |

**Recommended order:** `upload` → `verify-operations` → `verify-trust` → `verify-governance` → `lifecycle`

Governance packs live under `integration/{{appName}}/scenarios/` (YAML). `aifabrix upload {{appName}}` publishes them to the dataplane; `verify-governance` uses those persisted packs by default (`--pack` is for authoring overrides only).

```bash
aifabrix upload {{appName}}

aifabrix verify-operations {{appName}}
aifabrix verify-operations {{appName}} -v

aifabrix verify-trust {{appName}} -v
aifabrix verify-trust {{appName}} --no-sync --revalidate

aifabrix verify-governance {{appName}} -v
aifabrix verify-governance {{appName}} --no-sync

# Report only (GET persisted results)
aifabrix lifecycle {{appName}}
aifabrix lifecycle {{appName}} -v

# Run missing verify steps, publish local files, then print report
aifabrix lifecycle {{appName}} --run
aifabrix lifecycle {{appName}} --run --no-sync
```

**Prerequisites:** `aifabrix login`, dataplane reachable, config published (`upload`). Governance also needs identity sync, protection upload, fixture load, and `governance:evaluate` on your token — see your scenario pack README or platform docs.

**Single-datasource trust** (same semantic check as system `verify-trust`, one key):

```bash
aifabrix datasource verify-trust {{#if hasDatasources}}{{datasources.[0].datasourceKey}}{{else}}<datasource-key>{{/if}} --app {{appName}} -v
```

Common flags: `-v` / `--verbose`, `-d` / `--debug` (trust), `--no-sync` (skip pre-run upload), `--json` (machine-readable envelope).

## Debug and low-level tests

Advanced commands for architects and CI. Prefer [Enterprise AI Certification](#enterprise-ai-certification) for integrator proof unless you need step-by-step debugging.

| Command | Network | Notes |
| --- | --- | --- |
| `aifabrix validate {{appName}}` | Off | Schemas and files only |
| `aifabrix test {{appName}}` | Off | Local checks |
| `aifabrix test-integration {{appName}}` | On | Needs login + dataplane |
| `aifabrix test-e2e {{appName}}` | On | E2E for every datasource; uploads local files first unless `--no-sync` |

System-level tests publish local integration files before the run (same path as `upload`). Use **`--no-sync`** to validate against config already on the dataplane.

```bash
aifabrix test-e2e {{appName}} --no-sync -d
```

Single datasource E2E:

{{#if hasDatasources}}
```bash
{{#each datasources}}
# {{displayName}}
aifabrix datasource test-e2e {{datasourceKey}} --app {{../appName}}

{{/each}}
```
{{else}}
```bash
aifabrix datasource test-e2e <datasource-key> --app {{appName}}
```
{{/if}}

Common flags: `-v` / `--verbose`, `-d` / `--debug`, `--no-async` (datasource E2E only), `--no-sync` (skip pre-run upload on system `test-e2e`).

Debug logs (when using `--debug` on datasource commands) are written under `integration/{{appName}}/logs/` — use `aifabrix datasource log-test`, `log-integration`, `log-e2e`, or `log-trust` to inspect the latest file for each type.

